cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.DS

The paper discusses machine learning and deep learning innovations and proposes a framework for model evaluation and benchmarking. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the lack of standard and efficient ways of specifying and provisioning ML/DL evaluation, which could fall under the sub-category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the implementation of the framework with support for all major frameworks and hardware, which could fall under the sub-category of Software Engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper mentions performing parallel evaluation and how HW/SW stack choices affect performance, which could fall under the sub-category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS).
